==English==
===Etymology===

16th Century, via [[Latin]] from [[Greek]], from ''[[elephas]]''. ''Elephant'' + ''iasis''.

===Noun===
'''elephantiasis'''

#(In [[Pathology]]) A complication of [[chronic]] [[filariasis]], in which [[nematode]] worms block the [[lymphatic]] vessels, ususally in the legs or [[scrotum]], causing extreme enlargement of the infected area.